Juanín García.label: Juanín García
Juanín García.description: Juan García Lorenzana, known as Juanín García, is a Spanish handball player. He currently plays for Barcelona, with whom he won the Champions League in 2011 in the finale against Ciudad Real. Wikipedia

Konstantin Igropulo.label: Konstantin Igropulo
Konstantin Igropulo.description:
Konstantin Igropulo is a Russian handballer who plays for Füchse Berlin and the Russian national team.
He competed at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, where the Russian team placed sixth. Wikipedia

Kiril Lazarov.label: Kiril Lazarov
Kiril Lazarov.description: Kiril "Kire" Lazarov is a Macedonian handball player who currently plays for Barcelona Handbol. He is also the captain of the Macedonia national handball team. Wikipedia
Kiril Lazarov.Born: May 10, 1980 (age 33), Sveti Nikole, Republic of Macedonia

Louise Spellerberg.label: Louise Spellerberg
Louise Spellerberg.description:
Louise Spellerberg is a Danish handballer who plays for FC Midtjylland Håndbold.
She is also member of the Danish national team, and participated at the 2011 World Women's Handball Championship in Brazil. Wikipedia

Magnus Jernemyr.label: Magnus Jernemyr
Magnus Jernemyr.description: Magnus Jernemyr is a Swedish handballer who plays for LUGI HF and the Swedish national team. In 2012, he was selected as Liga ASOBAL's best defender. Wikipedia

Begoña Fernández.label: Begoña Fernández
Begoña Fernández.description: Begoña Fernández Molinos is a Spanish team handball player. She currently plays for the club ŽRK Vardar and on the Spanish national team. Wikipedia

Ágota Bujdosó.label: Ágota Bujdosó
Ágota Bujdosó.description: Ágota Bujdosó is a former Hungarian international handball goalkeeper. Wikipedia

Eszter Mátéfi.label: Eszter Mátéfi
Eszter Mátéfi.description: Eszter Mátéfi is a handball coach and former handball player who works as the head coach of the handball academy in Dunaújváros. Wikipedia

Amália Sterbinszky.label: Amália Sterbinszky
Amália Sterbinszky.description:
Amália Sterbinszky is a former Hungarian handball player who was voted the best female handballer of the twentieth century in Hungary.
She competed in two Olympic Games, winning the bronze medal in the first one. Wikipedia

Marianna Nagy (handballer).label: Marianna Nagy
Marianna Nagy (handballer).description: Marianna Nagy is a former Hungarian handball player and Olympic medalist. Wikipedia

Dijana Števin.label: Dijana Števin
Dijana Števin.description: Dijana Števin is a Serbian handballer who plays for the French club HBC Nimes on loan from ŽRK Budućnost Podgorica. She is also member of the Serbian national team. Wikipedia

Ștefan Birtalan.label: Ștefan Birtalan
Ștefan Birtalan.description:
Ştefan Birtalan is a former Romanian handball player, coach and sports official.
Birtalan, who comes form the Hungarian minority in Romania, was one of the best players of his time and was named the World Player of the Year in 1974, 1976 and 1977. Wikipedia

Joan Cañellas.label: Joan Cañellas
Joan Cañellas.description: Joan Cañellas Reixach is a Spanish handballer who plays for HSV Hamburg and the Spanish national team. While playing in Madrid, he also studied pharmacy at Universidad Complutense de Madrid. Wikipedia
Joan Cañellas.Born: September 30, 1986 (age 27), Santa Maria de Palautordera, Spain

Pelle Linders.label: Pelle Linders
Pelle Linders.description: Pelle Linders is a Swedish handball player, currently playing for Danish Handball League side FCK Håndbold, with whom he won the Danish Championship in 2008. Wikipedia

Eduardo Gurbindo.label: Eduardo Gurbindo
Eduardo Gurbindo.description: Eduardo Gurbindo Martínez is a Spanish handballer who played for BM Valladolid until 2012 when he moved to FC Barcelona Handbol and the Spanish national team. Wikipedia

Dejan Manaskov.label: Dejan Manaskov
Dejan Manaskov.description:
Dejan Manaskov is a Macedonian handball player who currently plays for RK Metalurg Skopje and for the Macedonia national handball team.
He is the older son of Pepi Manaskov. Wikipedia

Boris Schnuchel.label: Boris Schnuchel
Boris Schnuchel.description:
Boris Schnuchel is a Danish handballer, currently playing for Danish Handball League side KIF Kolding, with whom he has played since 1997 and won 5 Danish Championships.
Schnuchel has played 31 matches with the Danish national handball team. Wikipedia

Dennis Mathiasen.label: Dennis Mathiasen
Dennis Mathiasen.description: Dennis Mathiasen is a Danish handballer, currently playing for Danish Handball League side Skjern Håndbold. He has played in the club for the past eight years, and was a part of the team as they won the EHF Challenge Cup in 2002 and 2003 Wikipedia

Ágnes Hornyák.label: Ágnes Hornyák
Ágnes Hornyák.description:
Ágnes Hornyák is a Hungarian handballer playing for Győri Audi ETO KC and the Hungarian national team.
She mader her international debut against Norway on 2 March 2005. Wikipedia

Elisabeth Pinedo.label: Elisabeth Pinedo
Elisabeth Pinedo.description:
Elisabeth Pinedo is a Spanish handball player.
She was part of the Spanish team at the 2008 European Women's Handball Championship, where the Spanish team reached the final, after defeating Germany in the semifinal. Wikipedia

Mariama Signaté.label: Mariama Signaté
Mariama Signaté.description: Mariama Signaté is a French handball player. She plays for the French handball club Issy-Paris Hand and for the French national team. Wikipedia

Marco Oneto.label: Marco Oneto
Marco Oneto.description: Marco Antonio Oneto Zúñiga is a professional handball player, and a captain of Chilean handball team. He plays for Magdeburg Wikipedia

Anja Edin.label: Anja Edin
Anja Edin.description: Anja Hammerseng-Edin is a Norwegian handball player. She currently plays for Larvik HK and the Norwegian national team. Wikipedia

Anna Loerper.label: Anna Loerper
Anna Loerper.description:
Anna Loerper is a German handball player. She plays for the club VfL Oldenburg and for the German national team.

Cléopâtre Darleux.label: Cléopâtre Darleux
Cléopâtre Darleux.description:
Cléopatre Darleux is a French handball goalkeeper. She plays for the club Viborg HK and for the French national team.
She participated at the 2009 World Women's Handball Championship in China, winning a silver medal with the French team. Wikipedia

Claudine Mendy.label: Claudine Mendy
Claudine Mendy.description: Claudine Mendy is a French handball player. She plays for the club Metz Handball and for the French national team. In the upcoming 2012-2013 season the left back will play for ŽRK Budućnost. Wikipedia

Daniel Żółtak.label: Daniel Żółtak
Daniel Żółtak.description: Daniel Żółtak is a Polish handball player and a member of Poland national handball team. He currently plays for the Polish club Vive Targi Kielce. His hobbies include web surfing, fishing and tennis. He is married. Wikipedia

Laura Steinbach.label: Laura Steinbach
Laura Steinbach.description: Laura Steinbach is a German handball player. She currently plays for the Hungarian club Ferencvárosi TC and for the German national team. Wikipedia

Inga Berit Svestad.label: Inga Berit Svestad
Inga Berit Svestad.description:
Inga Berit Svestad is a Norwegian handball player. She currently plays for Byåsen HE, and on the Norwegian national team.

Mouna Chebbah.label: Mouna Chebbah
Mouna Chebbah.description: Mouna Chebbah is a Tunisian handballer who is part of the Tunisian national team. She is also a member of Danish club Viborg HK from 1 July 2010. Wikipedia

Piotr Wyszomirski.label: Piotr Wyszomirski
Piotr Wyszomirski.description: Piotr Wyszomirski is a Polish handball player and a member of Poland national handball team. He currently plays for the Hungarian club Csurgói KK. Wikipedia

Simona Spiridon.label: Simona Spiridon
Simona Spiridon.description: Simona Spiridon is a Romanian-Austrian handballer who plays for the Austrian club Hypo Niederösterreich. She is also member of the Austrian national team. Wikipedia

Siri Seglem.label: Siri Seglem
Siri Seglem.description:
Siri Seglem is a Norwegian handball player. She currently plays for Aalborg DH, and on the Norwegian national team.

Borko Ristovski.label: Borko Ristovski

Tímea Tóth.label: Tímea Tóth
Tímea Tóth.description: Tímea Tóth is a Hungarian handballer who plays for Érdi VSE and the Hungarian national team. Wikipedia

Linnea Torstenson.label: Linnea Torstenson
Linnea Torstenson.description: Linnea Torstenson is a Swedish female handballer who plays as a left back for Viborg HK and the Sweden national team. Wikipedia

Johanna Ahlm.label: Johanna Ahlm
Johanna Ahlm.description: Johanna Ahlm is a Swedish handball player who has played for the Sweden women's national handball team. She competed at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing, where Sweden placed 8th. Wikipedia

Oana Manea.label: Oana Manea
Oana Manea.description: Oana Andreea Manea is a Romanian female handballer who plays as a line player for CSM București and the Romanian national team. Wikipedia

Olha Nikolayenko.label: Olha Nikolayenko
Olha Nikolayenko.description:
Olha Nikolayenko is a Ukrainian handballer who plays for Ferencvárosi TC and the Ukrainian national team.

Patricia Vizitiu.label: Patricia Vizitiu
Patricia Vizitiu.description: Patricia Maria Vizitiu is a Romanian female handballer who plays for CSM București. Wikipedia

Regina Shymkute.label: Regina Shymkute
Regina Shymkute.description: Regina Shymkute is a Ukrainian-born Russian handballer playing for Rostov-Don. Wikipedia

Allison Pineau.label: Allison Pineau
Allison Pineau.description: Allison Pineau is a French handballer who plays for the French national team. She was voted World Handball Player of the Year 2009 by the International Handball Federation. Wikipedia

Ágnes Triffa.description:
Ágnes Triffa is a Hungarian handball goalkeeper who plays for Váci NKSE and the Hungarian national team.

Anita Kazai.label: Anita Kazai
Anita Kazai.description: Anita Kazai is a Hungarian handballer who plays for Debreceni VSC in left wing position. Wikipedia

Piroska Szamoránsky.label: Piroska Szamoránsky
Piroska Szamoránsky.description: Piroska Szamoránsky is a Hungarian handball player currently under contract with Ferencvárosi TC. Wikipedia

Václav Straka.label: Václav Straka

Zsuzsanna Tomori.label: Zsuzsanna Tomori
Zsuzsanna Tomori.description: Zsuzsanna Tomori is a Hungarian handballer who plays for Ferencvárosi TC and the Hungarian national team. Wikipedia

Anja Andersen.label: Anja Andersen
Anja Andersen.description: Anja Andersen is a female former handball player and currently coach. Wikipedia
Awards: IHF World Player of the Year - Women

Erhard Wunderlich.label: Erhard Wunderlich
Erhard Wunderlich.description:
Erhard "Sepp" Wunderlich was a German handball player.
Wunderlich was born in Augsburg. As a member of the West German handball team, he won the 1978 World Men's Handball Championship and the silver medal at the 1984 Summer Olympics. Wikipedia

Lotte Kiærskou.label: Lotte Kiærskou
Lotte Kiærskou.description: Lotte Kiærskou is a Danish team handball player and two times Olympic champion. She won a gold medal with the Danish national team at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, and again four years later at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens. Wikipedia

Rikke Skov.label: Rikke Skov
Rikke Skov.description: Rikke Skov is a Danish handball player and Olympic champion. She received a gold medal with the Danish national team at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens. Wikipedia

Harry Winkler (handballer).label: Harry Winkler
Harry Winkler (handballer).description: Harry William Winkler, Jr. is an American former Olympic handballer and retired school teacher. He was also a member of the U.S. Men's Handball Team at the 1972 Summer Olympics and the U.S. Men's Handball ... Wikipedia

Mirko Alilović.label: Mirko Alilović
Mirko Alilović.description: Mirko Alilović is a Croatian handball goalkeeper who plays for KC Veszprém. He is also member of the Croatia national handball team, with them he won the silver medals both on the World Championship and the European Championship. Wikipedia

Péter Kovács (handballer).label: Péter Kovács
Péter Kovács (handballer).description: Péter Kovács is a former Hungarian international handball player and handball coach, currently in charge by Békéscsabai Előre NKSE. Wikipedia

André Jørgensen.label: André Jørgensen
André Jørgensen.description: André Jørgensen is a Norwegian handball player, currently playing for Danish Handball League side AaB Håndbold. Before joining AaB, Jørgensen played for the Spanish team CD Bidasoa. Wikipedia

Anja Althaus.label: Anja Althaus
Anja Althaus.description:
Anja Althaus is a German handballer playing for ŽRK Vardar and the German national team. She won the Champions League with Viborg in 2009.
Althaus made her debut on the German team in 2002. She received a bronze medal at the 2007 World Championship. Wikipedia

Erlend Mamelund.label: Erlend Mamelund
Erlend Mamelund.description: Erlend Mamelund is a Norwegian team handball player. Wikipedia

Hege Kvitsand.label: Hege Kvitsand
Hege Kvitsand.description: Hege Kristine Kvitsand is a Norwegian handball player who played for the club Bækkelagets SK and the Norwegian national team in the 1990s. She was born in Trondheim. Wikipedia

Kristine Moldestad.label: Kristine Moldestad
Kristine Moldestad.description: Kristine Moldestad is a Norwegian handball player who played for the club Larvik HK and the Norwegian national team in the 1990s. She was born in Bærum. She competed at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, where the Norwegian team finished fourth. Wikipedia

Ida Bjørndalen.label: Ida Bjørndalen
Ida Bjørndalen.description: Ida Bjørndalen is a Norwegian handballer playing for KIF Vejen and occasionally for the Norwegian national team. She won the Champions League with Viborg HK in 2009. Wikipedia

Linn Jørum Sulland.label: Linn Jørum Sulland
Linn Jørum Sulland.description: Linn Jørum Sulland is a Norwegian handballer playing for Larvik HK. She also participates in the handball and beach handball national teams. Until July 2009 she played for Stabæk IF. Wikipedia

Nadine Krause.label: Nadine Krause
Nadine Krause.description: Nadine Krause is a German handballer who plays for TSV Bayer Leverkusen as a left back. She made her debut on the German A-Team in 1999, at the age of 17. Wikipedia
Awards: IHF World Player of the Year - Women

Nina Wörz.label: Nina Wörz
Nina Wörz.description: Nina Wörz is a German handball player. She plays for the Slovenian club Krim and for the German national team, having made her international debut on 19 February 1999 against Poland. Wikipedia

Renate Urne.label: Renate Urne
Renate Urne.description: Renate Urne is a retired Norwegian international handballer. She played in her native Norway for Erdal IL, IL Bjørnar and Tertnes HE, before moving to German side HC Leipzig in 2007. She stayed in Leipzig until her retirement in 2011. Wikipedia

Ole Magnus Ekelund.label: Ole Magnus Ekelund
Ole Magnus Ekelund.description: Ole Magnus Ekelund is a Norwegian handball player, currently playing for Danish Handball League side FCK Håndbold. Wikipedia

Sławomir Szmal.label: Sławomir Szmal
Sławomir Szmal.description: Sławomir Szmal is a Polish handball player and a member of Poland national handball team. In Poland, he played for Warszawianka Warszawa and Orlen Płock. Currently he plays for the Polish team Vive Targi Kielce. Wikipedia

Steinar Ege.label: Steinar Ege
Steinar Ege.description: Steinar Ege is a Norwegian handballer, currently playing as a goalkeeper for the Danish Handball League side AG København. He has previously played for the German Bundesliga clubs THW Kiel and VfL Gummersbach. Wikipedia

Terese Pedersen.label: Terese Pedersen
Terese Pedersen.description:
Terese Pedersen is a Norwegian handball goalkeeper. She currently plays for Byåsen HE in Norway.
She started her club career in Larvik, and has also played for Runar, Sandar, Tertnes, and Randers HK. Wikipedia

Tine Rustad Kristiansen.label: Tine Rustad Kristiansen
Tine Rustad Kristiansen.description:
Tine Rustad Kristiansen is a Norwegian handball player. She currently plays for Larvik HK, and on the Norwegian national team.
She made her debut on the Norwegian national team in 2005, and has played 43 matches and scored 52 goals. Wikipedia

Allahkaram Esteki.label: Allahkaram Esteki
Allahkaram Esteki.description:
Allahkaram Esteki is an Iranian professional handball player who currently plays for Foolad Mobarakeh Sepahan.
Esteki was previously on trial with German club VfL Gummersbach in the Bundesliga.
Esteki also represents the Iran national handball team. Wikipedia

Julija Portjanko.label: Julija Portjanko
Julija Portjanko.description: Julija Portjanko, also Julija Nikolić is a Macedonian handball player. She plays for the club ŽRK Vardar and for the Macedonia women's national handball team. Wikipedia

Vladimir Temelkov.label: Vladimir Temelkov
Vladimir Temelkov.description: Vladimir Temelkov is a Macedonian handball player who plays for HC Bascharage, and for the Macedonia national handball team. Wikipedia

Clara Vădineanu.label: Clara Vădineanu
Clara Vădineanu.description: Clara Vădineanu is a Romanian handballer. Wikipedia

Nenad Puljezević.label: Nenad Puljezevic
Nenad Puljezević.description: Nenad Puljezević is an Serbian-born Hungarian handball goalkeeper, who plays for TSV Hannover-Burgdorf and the Hungarian national team. He is under contract with the German team until summer 2012. Wikipedia

Cédric Sorhaindo.label: Cédric Sorhaindo
Cédric Sorhaindo.description: Cédric Sorhaindo is a French team handball player. He played on the France national handball team which won gold medals at the 2009 World Men's Handball Championship in Croatia. Wikipedia

Alexander Radčenko.label: Alexander Radčenko
Alexander Radčenko.description: Alexander Radčenko is a Czech handball player, currently playing for HT Tatran Prešov in the Slovak Extraliga. He also plays for the Czech national handball team. Wikipedia

Anastasiya Pidpalova.label: Anastasiya Pidpalova
Anastasiya Pidpalova.description: Anastasiya Pidpalova is a Ukrainian handballer playing for Dinamo Volgograd and the Ukrainian national team. Wikipedia

Enid Tahirović.label: Enid Tahirovic
Enid Tahirović.description: Enid Tahirović is a Bosnian handballer. He is one of the top goalkeepers in the Bundesliga. Currently he plays in Germany for HSV Hamburg, after having spent four seasons at Frisch Auf Göppingen. Wikipedia

Mirsad Terzić.label: Mirsad Terzić
Mirsad Terzić.description: Mirsad Terzić is a Bosnian professional handballer, and the current captain of national team. Currently he plays in Hungary for MKB Veszprém KC. Wikipedia

Muhamed Mustafić.label: Muhamed Mustafić
Muhamed Mustafić.description: Muhamed Mustafić is a Bosnian professional handballer. Currently, he plays in North Cyprus for Turkish Hanball Super Lig team S.K Besaparmak. Wikipedia

Muhamed Toromanović.label: Muhamed Toromanović
Muhamed Toromanović.description: Muhamed Toromanović is a Bosnian handballer who currently plays for Wisła Płock in Poland and the Bosnia national handball team. Wikipedia

Nebojša Grahovac.label: Nebojša Grahovac
Nebojša Grahovac.description: Nebojša Grahovac is a Bosnian professional handballer. Currently, he plays in France for Chambéry Savoie Handball. He plays as goalkeeper, and is current member of Bosnia and Herzegovina national handball team. Wikipedia

Nikola Prce.label: Nikola Prce
Nikola Prce.description: Nikola Prce is a Bosnian professional handballer, playing as left back. Currently he plays in Hungary for | Szeged. In season 2008-09 when playing for SD Octavio Vigo he was third best goal scorer of Liga ASOBAL with 181 goal. Wikipedia

Radoslav Antl.label: Radoslav Antl
Radoslav Antl.description: Radoslav Antl is a Slovak handball player, currently playing for HT Tatran Prešov in the Slovak Extraliga. He also plays for the Slovak national handball team. Wikipedia

Tomasz Rosiński.label: Tomasz Rosiński
Tomasz Rosiński.description: Tomasz Rosiński is a Polish handball player and a member of Poland national handball team. He currently plays for the Polish club Vive Targi Kielce. Wikipedia

Christopher McDermott.label: Christopher McDermott
Christopher McDermott.description: Christopher McDermott is a British Handball player. He competed as part of Team GB at the 2012 London Olympic Games. He currently plays for Salford H.C. Wikipedia

Abdullah Al-Wuhaib.label: Abdullah Al-Wuhaib
Abdullah Al-Wuhaib.description: Abdullah Al-Wuhaib ‎ was a Saudi Arabian handball player, who played in Al-Arabi, he achieved several accomplishments,with his team and played from 1974 till 1993.In 2009 biography about him was published by the name Wuhaiba the iron hand. Wikipedia

Adriana Ţăcălie.label: Adriana Ţăcălie
Adriana Ţăcălie.description: Adriana-Gabriela Țăcălie is a Romanian handballer who plays for ASC Corona Braşov and the Romanian national team. Wikipedia

Ana Gros.label: Ana Gros
Ana Gros.description: Ana Gros is a Slovenian handballer who plays for Metz HB in right back position. She is also member of the Slovenian national team. Wikipedia

Anett Kisfaludy.label: Anett Kisfaludy
Anett Kisfaludy.description:
Anett Kisfaludy is a Hungarian handballer who currently plays for Érdi VSE.
She was selected for the Hungarian national team first time in the friendly tournament Pannon Cup, and made her international debut on 24 April 2011 against Brazil. Wikipedia

Anikó Szamoránsky.label: Anikó Szamoránsky
Anikó Szamoránsky.description: Anikó Szamoránsky is a Hungarian handball player who currently plays for Kiskunhalas NKSE. Wikipedia

Beáta Bohus.label: Beáta Bohus
Beáta Bohus.description: Beáta Bohus is a Hungarian handball player and handball coach. She plays for Csorvási SK in the Hungarian second division, and beside her playing duties she also had coaching roles by her former club Békéscsabai Előre NKSE. Wikipedia

Woo Sun-Hee.label: Woo Sun-Hee
Woo Sun-Hee.description:
Woo Sun-Hee is a female South Korean handball player.
In 2003, Woo competed in the World Women's Handball Championship held in Croatia and led her team to the bronze medal. She was finally named to the All-Star team of the competition. Wikipedia
